• 3,500 solar modules covering 6,100 m² generate 1,300 MWh electricity per year

• ~3,000 metric tons of CO2e will already be saved in FY24 due to heat supply optimization

• 100% renewable energy sources: Heat pumps and lake water for cooling and heating

• Net zero planned by 2025 driven by energy efficiency measures (heat recovery), heat pumps and renewable district heating

• Siemens Digital twin and latest building technology for state-of-the-art laboratories